<div class="page-header mtn pbn">
  <figure class="jumbotron ptn pbn" style="background-color: black;">
    <%=image_tag('welcome-banner.jpg', class: 'center-block', style: 'height:200px;')%>
  </figure>
</div>

<div class="row maxl">
  <section class="col-lg-6">
    <h2 class="mtl">Overwhelmed?</h4>
    <p>
      Valoritization is a simple tool to step back and find where to start. It works for every situation where you have too much on your plate; if you want an efficient way to deal with it, you just found it!
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>You need an easy way of getting everyone to agree on a plan?</li>
      <li>You have an exam tomorrow and you are 10 chapters behind?</li>
      <li>You have too many books that you want to read?</li>
      <li>You want to realize a personal project?</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      The best example might be this website himself. Indeed,
      <%=link_to 'I am using this website', :matrices %>
      to create it.
    </p>
    <p>
      Feel free to add a task you wish to be added to Valoritization.com
    </p>
  </section>
  <section class="col-lg-6">
    <div class="panel panel-default">
      <div class="panel-heading">
        <h4>Setup your matrix:</h4>
      </div>
      <div class="panel-body">
        <ol class="col-sm-4">
          <%= render partial: "notice_step", locals: { icon: 'cart-plus', number: 1, text: 'Choose your value metric'}%>
        </ol>
        <ol class="col-sm-4">
          <%= render partial: "notice_step", locals: { icon: 'industry', number: 2, text: 'Choose your cost metric'}%>
        </ol>
        <ol class="col-sm-4">
          <%= render partial: "notice_step", locals: { icon: 'list-ul', number: 3, text: 'List your tasks'}%>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="panel panel-default">
      <div class="panel-heading">
        <h4>Optimize your work:</h4>
      </div>
      <div class="panel-body">
        <ol class="col-sm-4">
          <%= render partial: "notice_step", locals: { icon: 'ban', number: 1, text: 'Identify the traps'}%>
        </ol>
        <ol class="col-sm-4">
          <%= render partial: "notice_step", locals: { icon: 'bolt', number: 2, text: 'Do the quick-wins'}%>
        </ol>
        <ol class="col-sm-4">
          <%= render partial: "notice_step", locals: { icon: 'cut', number: 3, text: 'Cut the bigger tasks'}%>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</div>
<section class="panel panel-default">
  <div class="panel-heading">
    <h4>You want to give it a try?</h4>
  </div>
  <div class="panel-body">
    <strong>No sign-up</strong>, just click! &nbsp;
    <%= link_to 'Create a new matrix', {action: :new, controller: :matrices}, class: 'btn btn-primary navbar-btn' %>
  </div>
</section>
